cargon
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:the cargon-system is a system of handling air-cargo, used by the Straits Air Freight Express Ltd and conceived by Mr T.M.A. O'Connell, General Manager: the aeroplane is built without a conventional floor, and rails are built into the fuselage and the cargon (or pallet), like a huge, wheeled tray, pre-packed with goods, is easily wheeled in or out of the aircraft (R. Mason). -
